{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=June 2018}} {{DISPLAYTITLE:''Anargha Nimisham''}} '''''Anargha Nimisham''''' (''Invaluable Moment'') is a collection of short stories by [[Vaikom Muhammad Basheer]] published in 1946.<ref>.[http://www.cs.nyu.edu/kandathi/basheer.html "Works by Vaikom Muhammad Basheer"]. [[New York University]]. Retrieved 3 June 2013.</ref> Unlike other works by Basheer which are filled with humour and satire, stories of ''Anargha Nimisham'' mostly deal with philosophical and spiritual aspects.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.hindu.com/fline/fl2502/stories/20080201501110100.htm |title=Sultan of story: A birth centenary tribute to Vaikom Mohammed Basheer who picked up his tales from life's poetry |author=[[Satchidanandan]] |journal=[[Frontline (magazine)|Frontline]] |date=February 2008 |volume= 25 |series= |issue= 2|accessdate=3 June 2013}}</ref>
